# CVE-2024-23342 refers to a vulnerability where:
# ECDSA (elliptic curve digital signature algorithm) operations may leak timing info
# The “Minerva” attack uses this to infer private keys — but only in very specific conditions
# It only applies when:
    # You’re generating or signing ECDSA keys
    # The attacker can observe very fine-grained timing differences
# Typically only affects smartcards, HSMs, embedded hardware, etc.
# So unless you’re:
    # Signing sensitive ECDSA keys at runtime with untrusted clients
    # Running inside a hardware device exposed to attackers
# ...you are almost certainly not at risk.
CVE-2024-23342
